A comprehensive Chinese culture and tourism promotion program was launched on Tuesday night in London. The launch of 2019 China Weeks -- When Culture and Tourism Blend -- was hosted at Cultural Office of the Chinese Embassy in the United Kingdom. From May to June, the China Weeks, consisting of 11 programs covering areas like performance, dialogue, lecture, concert, exhibition and promotion event, will be held across Britain. The highlights include world renowned choreographer Yang Liping's The Rite of Spring, which will be staged at the Sadler's Wells Theatre from May 9 to 11, a Philharmonia Orchestra Concert at Royal Festival Hall on May 11, the Amazing China exhibition at 2019 London Craft Week from May 10 to 12, and the signing of MOU between Britain's Tate Gallery and Shanghai's Pudong Museum of Art. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Delegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los AngelesChinese driving Vegas growthHaving fun